# Accepted infrastructure risks (reviewed). One Trivy AVD ID per line.
# These are deliberate, documented trade-offs — not oversights.

# AVD-AWS-0054 — ALB listeners serve plain HTTP (ports 80 prod / 8080 test).
# Accepted: TLS is the final planned phase; it needs a registered domain + ACM
# certificate. Tracked as the last roadmap item.
AVD-AWS-0054

# AVD-AWS-0104 — Security groups allow egress to 0.0.0.0/0.
# Accepted: ECS Fargate tasks need outbound access to pull images from ECR and to
# read credentials from Secrets Manager / call AWS APIs. Locking egress down would
# require VPC interface endpoints for ECR, Secrets Manager, CloudWatch, etc.
AVD-AWS-0104
